    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If you install 6.0 on Python 2 is does already do that with a big:\r\n\"UPGRADE PIP\", [ok maybe not uppercase](https://github.com/ipython/ipython/blob/master/setup.py#L44-L55), \r\nbut AFAICT IPython download on pip < 6 [are low](https://github.com/Carreau/miscs/blob/master/IPython-dls.ipynb). (I need to rerun that with all the pip versions, but at least you can see the code that did it).\r\n\r\nThere is still pip 1.6 around because that's what ubuntu 16.04 LTS has, so failing on critically old pip with a reason why and tell users to upgrade pip is (I think) something to consider. \r\n\r\nI'm obviously not the only one to decide, but It might be a reasonable thing to do."
